Beretta A300 Outlander is a gas operated Semi-Auto Shotgun that uses a compensating exhaust valve allowing the shotgun to cycle a wide range of ammunition, from 2-3/4" target loads to 3" magnum waterfowl loads. The A300 Outlander semi-automatic shotgun breaks down into 4 major components, making it quick and tool-free to fieldstrip, even under adverse conditions. The barrel of the A300 is chrome lined, and uses standard Beretta Mobilchoke®. The barrel comes with a ventilated rib and bead sight, and the receiver is grooved to accept aftermarket optical sights. The Beretta A300 Outlander is a great value for a versatile, ultra reliable Semi-Auto Shotgun that's well suited for hunting waterfowl, turkeys, and upland game. Made in USA.
